234
00:23:22,321 --> 00:23:25,192
That's emergency.
They run on AC like the signals.

235
00:23:25,324 --> 00:23:26,237
Atchoo!

236
00:23:26,367 --> 00:23:28,075
- Stop that, will you?
- Sorry.

237
00:23:28,202 --> 00:23:30,076
Command Centre calling Pelham.

238
00:23:30,204 --> 00:23:35,660
Did you cut off the power down there?
Without callin' to explain? Listen to me.

239
00:23:36,377 --> 00:23:39,461
You've screwed up the
whole subway system.

240
00:23:43,551 --> 00:23:46,255
Gentlemen, this is
the TA Command Centre.

241
00:23:46,387 --> 00:23:48,712
A lot of laughs in here. Terrific place.

242
00:23:48,848 --> 00:23:53,675
Each train is identified by the name of
its terminus and the time of its departure.

243
00:23:53,811 --> 00:23:59,517
Thus an express train leavin' Woodlawn
at 6.30pm would be Woodlawn 6-3-0.

244
00:23:59,650 --> 00:24:05,273
While on its return trip its destination
might be... let's say Flatbush 8-2-5.

245
00:24:05,406 --> 00:24:09,902
- I hope you're memorisin' all this junk.
- Garber, what's the matter with you?

246
00:24:10,035 --> 00:24:12,324
Don't worry.
They don't understand English.

247
00:24:12,454 --> 00:24:14,910
This way, dummies.
Step this way, dummies.

248
00:24:15,040 --> 00:24:21,209
Over here is Frank Correll, the Lord Byron
of the New York City Subway System.

249
00:24:21,338 --> 00:24:24,125
Observe the way fire and smoke
shoot out of his ears.

250
00:24:24,258 --> 00:24:26,749
Don't bug me, Garber. I got troubles here.

251
00:24:26,885 --> 00:24:30,966
A train is down, its radio's dead,
the power's off, and it's dumped its load.

252
00:24:31,098 --> 00:24:32,972
Aside from that, it's ginger-peachy.

253
00:24:36,145 --> 00:24:38,137
What time is it, Mr Green?

254
00:24:38,272 --> 00:24:40,146
Uh...

255
00:24:40,274 --> 00:24:42,350
2.10.

256
00:24:46,822 --> 00:24:50,072
Right. Time to talk to them.

257
00:24:51,744 --> 00:24:54,828
- Is something troubling you?
- I think I'm gonna die today.

258
00:24:54,955 --> 00:24:56,864
That's entirely possible.

259
00:25:02,087 --> 00:25:04,578
This is Pelham One Two Three
to Command Centre.

260
00:25:04,715 --> 00:25:08,582
This is Pelham One Two Three to
Command Centre. Do you read me?

261
00:25:08,719 --> 00:25:11,257
OK, we'll leave him alone to his problems.

262
00:25:11,388 --> 00:25:15,172
What are you tryin' to do?
Screw up this entire railroad?

263
00:25:15,309 --> 00:25:19,176
- I want an explanation! It better be good!
- Your train has been taken.

264
00:25:19,813 --> 00:25:22,684
- What?
- Repeat, your train has been taken.

265
00:25:22,816 --> 00:25:25,687
Hey, shut up in here! Shut up!

266
00:25:25,819 --> 00:25:27,942
I said shut it, everybody!

267
00:25:28,072 --> 00:25:30,693
Shut it up, everybody, goddamnit!

268
00:25:31,408 --> 00:25:33,366
The train has been taken?

269
00:25:33,494 --> 00:25:35,451
- Are you the motorman?
- Negative.

270
00:25:35,579 --> 00:25:40,241
Nobody's authorised to be in that cab
except the motorman. Identify yourself.

271
00:25:41,001 --> 00:25:46,078
Your locomotive has been hijacked
by a group of heavily armed men.

272
00:25:50,511 --> 00:25:52,053
It what?

273
00:25:52,179 --> 00:25:56,758
We are holding 17 passengers and
the conductor hostage in the first car.

274
00:25:57,601 --> 00:26:00,555
I am quite prepared to kill any
or all of them

275
00:26:00,688 --> 00:26:03,226
if you do not obey my commands
to the letter.

276
00:26:03,357 --> 00:26:07,485
- Have I made myself quite clear?
- You're outta your skull!

277
00:26:07,611 --> 00:26:11,561
Be that as it may, get out a pen,
take down our list of demands.

278
00:26:11,907 --> 00:26:14,694
Hey, now wait a minute.
Hold on. Stand by.

279
00:26:14,827 --> 00:26:17,578
Why would anybody hijack
a goddamn subway train?

280
00:26:17,705 --> 00:26:21,287
Hit your six button, Frank.
I want the TA police in on this.

281
00:26:21,417 --> 00:26:23,990
What are all these Chinamen
doin' in here?

282
00:26:24,128 --> 00:26:25,622
Holy Christ, I forgot.

283
00:26:25,754 --> 00:26:28,245
Charlie, take these monkeys up to 13.

284
00:26:28,382 --> 00:26:33,673
It is all right, Lieutenant Garber.
I am sure we can find it by ourselves.

285
00:26:37,099 --> 00:26:39,970
Thank you for a most
instructive visit, Lieutenant.

286
00:26:40,102 --> 00:26:43,056
A most exciting tour, Lieutenant.
Most exciting.

287
00:26:43,188 --> 00:26:45,228
Most exciting.

288
00:26:53,282 --> 00:26:55,322
Garber to Patrone. Garber to Patrone.

289
00:26:56,285 --> 00:26:58,325
Come in, Patrone.

290
00:26:58,787 --> 00:27:00,163
This is Patrone.

291
00:27:00,289 --> 00:27:04,915
Rico, I want you to plug everythin' you got
into the IRTtrain master's circuit.

292
00:27:05,044 --> 00:27:07,286
And all units stand by on the double.

293
00:27:07,421 --> 00:27:11,419
Call in the City cops. Put it on a 911
so their computer gets it.

294
00:27:11,550 --> 00:27:13,044
What's up, Z?

295
00:27:13,177 --> 00:27:15,964
- You won't believe it.
- I'll believe anythin'.

296
00:27:16,096 --> 00:27:18,634
A train's been hijacked.

297
00:27:19,683 --> 00:27:20,597
I don't believe it.

298
00:27:34,698 --> 00:27:36,406
When did the power go?

299
00:27:36,533 --> 00:27:39,534
- Conductor, when did the power go?
- Who wants to know?

300
00:27:39,662 --> 00:27:43,078
Me! The supervisor of the Grand
Central Tower wants to know!

301
00:27:43,207 --> 00:27:47,074
Oh, yes, sir! A couple of minutes ago!
Hey, what happened down there?

302
00:27:47,419 --> 00:27:49,708
Who wants to know!

303
00:27:49,964 --> 00:27:51,339
No, nobody's hurt!

304
00:27:51,465 --> 00:27:54,336
- What's goin' on?
- I don't know what's goin' on!

305
00:27:54,468 --> 00:27:56,675
- What happened?
- Nothin' happened, lady.

306
00:27:56,804 --> 00:27:58,595
- Anybody killed?
- Nobody's killed.

307
00:28:04,228 --> 00:28:07,644
On the left now, watch out for
the third rail. On the left now.

308
00:28:09,525 --> 00:28:12,312
What the hell is this, for Christ's sake?

309
00:28:15,239 --> 00:28:18,109
Your attention, please,
ladies and gentlemen.

310
00:28:18,242 --> 00:28:22,453
I'm sure the more intelligent of you
have worked out you're all hostages.

311
00:28:22,580 --> 00:28:24,619
Oh, my God!

312
00:28:26,041 --> 00:28:28,081
Isn't that wonderful

313
00:28:28,419 --> 00:28:31,254
- Hostages.
- What did you think? Guests?

314
00:28:31,380 --> 00:28:34,085
When we get what we want,
you'll be released unharmed.

315
00:28:34,216 --> 00:28:37,751
Until then, you'll continue to do
precisely as you're told.

316
00:28:43,225 --> 00:28:47,721
Excuse me, sir. What's going to happen
to us if you don't get what you want?

317
00:28:48,105 --> 00:28:52,317
Excuse me, sir. We are going
to get what we want.

318
00:28:55,196 --> 00:28:57,521
I don't give a damn
what they were armed with.

319
00:28:57,656 --> 00:28:59,732
They were gonna kill me!

320
00:28:59,867 --> 00:29:04,778
You're like the captain of the ship!
You're supposed to go down with it!

321
00:29:04,914 --> 00:29:07,535
- Horseshit!
- Oh, lady, butt out!

322
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:11,451
Tell Command Centre
I'll be on my way to investigate!

323
00:29:11,587 --> 00:29:14,623
I wouldn't go
down there if I was you!

324
00:29:14,757 --> 00:29:16,796
I know you wouldn't!

325
00:29:18,052 --> 00:29:23,294
You work for the subway, mister? Tell 'em
I'm gonna sue! I'm gonna sue their ass off!

326
00:29:30,439 --> 00:29:32,313
Pelham One Two Three
to Command Centre.

327
00:29:32,733 --> 00:29:35,936
Are you ready to take down
our list of demands?

328
00:29:36,070 --> 00:29:38,109
What do you want?

329
00:29:38,239 --> 00:29:40,694
- Do you have your pen?
- Go on, for Pete's sake!

330
00:29:42,243 --> 00:29:44,615
It's important you understand
three things.

331
00:29:44,745 --> 00:29:47,995
1) Pelham One Two Three is
completely within our control.

332
00:29:48,124 --> 00:29:50,661
2) We are all armed with
automatic weapons.

333
00:29:50,793 --> 00:29:53,414
3) We have no scruples about killing.

334
00:29:53,546 --> 00:29:57,757
- Do you understand me so far?
- I understand you fine, you lunatic.

335
00:29:58,217 --> 00:30:01,420
Inform the mayor that we demand
one million dollars cash

336
00:30:01,554 --> 00:30:04,341
for the release of the car
and all the hostages.

337
00:30:04,473 --> 00:30:07,889
- That'll be the day.
- The time is now 2.13.

338
00:30:08,102 --> 00:30:10,937
The money must be in our hands
not later than 3.13.

339
00:30:11,063 --> 00:30:12,641
One hour from now.

340
00:30:12,773 --> 00:30:17,601
If the money is not in our hands, we'll kill
one hostage for every minute you're late.

341
00:30:19,029 --> 00:30:20,607
Keep dreamin', maniac.

342
00:30:20,739 --> 00:30:24,358
If anybody attempts to interfere
- anyone, in any way -

343
00:30:24,493 --> 00:30:27,328
we will begin killing the hostages
immediately.

344
00:30:28,247 --> 00:30:29,410
Confirm, please.

345
00:30:29,540 --> 00:30:31,200
Zach! Zach!

346
00:30:31,333 --> 00:30:34,916
- Pelham One Two Three, come in, please.
- This is Pelham.

347
00:30:35,171 --> 00:30:37,377
Identify yourself, please.

348
00:30:37,506 --> 00:30:42,927
This is Lieutenant Zachary Garber of the
Transit Police. Identify yourself, please.

349
00:30:43,053 --> 00:30:45,011
I'm the man who stole your train.

350
00:30:45,139 --> 00:30:49,468
Sir, there is no way you can get away with
this. You are underground in a tunnel.

351
00:30:49,602 --> 00:30:51,594
Why concern yourself with that?

352
00:30:52,313 --> 00:30:55,729
At precisely 3.13 we are going
to begin executing the hostages.

353
00:30:55,858 --> 00:30:58,563
You'd better contact the mayor
and get back to me

354
00:30:58,694 --> 00:31:01,565
for my further instructions.
Over and out.

355
00:31:01,697 --> 00:31:04,698
Son of a bitch has got me backed up
all the way to the Bronx!

356
00:31:04,825 --> 00:31:07,233
What is this, a circus?
Let's get back to work!

357
00:31:07,369 --> 00:31:08,912
Rico, did you get that?

358
00:31:09,038 --> 00:31:12,407
I only got your end of it,
but I could piece it together. It's crazy.

359
00:31:12,541 --> 00:31:16,918
The guy's got a heavy English accent.
He could be a fruitcake.

360
00:31:17,046 --> 00:31:19,085
We got anybody at 28th Street?

361
00:31:20,424 --> 00:31:23,378
Just checkin' it out.
Yeah, he's around there somewhere.

362
00:31:23,510 --> 00:31:27,211
Tell him to hold the fort. Could be
all day before the City cops show up.

363
00:31:27,348 --> 00:31:29,636
They're never around when you need 'em.

364
00:31:31,852 --> 00:31:34,770
Lex 28. Lex 28. Come in, please.

365
00:31:35,773 --> 00:31:36,935
Patrolman James.

366
00:31:37,066 --> 00:31:40,067
This is Lieutenant Patrone.
Where are you?

367
00:31:40,194 --> 00:31:41,854
28th Street, southbound.

368
00:31:41,987 --> 00:31:46,815
Look, Lieutenant, everything's cooled out.
Nothing's happenin'. What's goin' on?

369
00:31:46,951 --> 00:31:50,284
Look, don't react to this,
but a train's been hijacked.

370
00:31:51,163 --> 00:31:53,950
- Holy shit.
- For God's sake, don't say anythin'.

371
00:31:54,083 --> 00:31:57,333
There's a supervisor from
Grand Central Tower.

372
00:31:57,461 --> 00:32:01,375
Yeah, I saw him a few minutes ago.
He went down the track on foot.

373
00:32:01,507 --> 00:32:03,998
Go after him.
See if you can turn him back.

374
00:32:04,134 --> 00:32:05,759
Yes, sir.

375
00:32:16,021 --> 00:32:20,730
All I know is I am the goddamn mayor
of the goddamn city of New York,

376
00:32:20,859 --> 00:32:24,644
the second most important
elective office in the entire country,

377
00:32:24,780 --> 00:32:29,241
and you tell me I gotta lay here and suffer
like every other schlub in the country?

378
00:32:29,368 --> 00:32:34,030
I'm sorry you have the flu, Mr Mayor.
There's nothing more I can do.

379
00:32:34,165 --> 00:32:37,533
There's one more thing. Get out!

380
00:32:39,753 --> 00:32:41,793
You can't fight City Hall.

381
00:32:50,389 --> 00:32:51,669
Yeah?

382
00:32:51,807 --> 00:32:55,508
Al, it's Warren. I'm comin' upstairs.
I got a real bitch on our hands.

383
00:32:55,644 --> 00:32:58,314
Don't tell me. I don't wanna know.

384
00:32:58,439 --> 00:33:01,938
- I'm comin' up.
- Can't you handle it, Warren?

385
00:33:02,067 --> 00:33:05,068
You are the goddamn
deputy mayor of the city of...

386
00:33:05,196 --> 00:33:09,240
Sure I can handle it. Like I handle
every other filthy, stinkin' job

387
00:33:09,366 --> 00:33:12,367
in this whole miserable city,
but I'm not gonna do it.

388
00:33:12,494 --> 00:33:14,571
What is it? Another strike?

389
00:33:14,705 --> 00:33:17,789
All right, all right.
I can take another strike.

390
00:33:17,916 --> 00:33:20,917
A gang of men has hijacked
a subway train.

391
00:33:21,795 --> 00:33:23,622
A gang of men...?

392
00:33:23,756 --> 00:33:28,050
Has hijacked a subway train.
They want a million dollars for it.

393
00:33:29,803 --> 00:33:31,843
Come on up.

394
00:33:35,684 --> 00:33:40,761
Couple number one are the winners
of today's newlywed gamel

395
00:33:41,273 --> 00:33:42,732
Missed it!

396
00:34:00,793 --> 00:34:02,702
What do you want, Mr Green?

397
00:34:02,836 --> 00:34:04,794
Is everythin' OK?

398
00:34:04,922 --> 00:34:09,251
Go and sit down. I do not want Mr Grey
and Mr Brown alone with the passengers.

399
00:34:09,385 --> 00:34:12,136
- Don't you trust them?
- I trust Mr Brown.

400
00:34:12,471 --> 00:34:14,760
I do not trust Mr Grey.

401
00:34:14,890 --> 00:34:18,888
I think that Mr Grey is an enormous
arrogant pain in the arse

402
00:34:19,019 --> 00:34:20,977
who could turn out to be trouble.

403
00:34:21,438 --> 00:34:23,478
I also think that he is mad.

404
00:34:24,483 --> 00:34:27,650
Why do you think
they threw him out of the Mafia?

405
00:34:27,778 --> 00:34:29,818
Ohh, terrific.

406
00:34:42,584 --> 00:34:45,372
- Hold it right there, cowboy!
- Who are you?!

407
00:34:45,504 --> 00:34:48,458
You'll find out
if you take another step!

408
00:34:48,591 --> 00:34:53,383
I'm warnin' ya, mister! That's City
property you're foolin' around with!

409
00:34:53,887 --> 00:34:55,382
That's just too fuckin' bad!

410
00:34:55,514 --> 00:34:59,132
Why don't you go grab a goddamn
aeroplane like everybody else?

411
00:34:59,268 --> 00:35:02,803
Cos we're afraid of flyin'!
Clear out or I'll shoot your ass off!

412
00:35:02,938 --> 00:35:05,560
The hell with you! I'm comin' on board!

413
00:35:06,150 --> 00:35:08,189
I warned you, stupid!

414
00:35:14,199 --> 00:35:16,239
Holy shit!

415
00:35:20,581 --> 00:35:23,451
I warned the bastard,
but he kept on comin' anyway.

416
00:35:23,584 --> 00:35:26,668
- Was he alone?
- I didn't see nobody else.

417
00:35:26,795 --> 00:35:27,744
Mr Brown.

418
00:35:27,880 --> 00:35:30,881
I guess I got us on the scoreboard, right?

419
00:35:35,095 --> 00:35:36,969
Take over from Mr Grey.

420
00:35:37,097 --> 00:35:40,716
- A little quick with that gun.
- The jerk was comin' on board!

421
00:35:40,851 --> 00:35:42,559
Loved every minute of it.

422
00:35:42,687 --> 00:35:46,020
- Keep those children quiet.
- I'm trying! I can't!

423
00:35:46,148 --> 00:35:49,268
- Do you want me to try?
- Oh, my God! No!

424
00:35:50,736 --> 00:35:52,729
You said nobody was gonna get hurt.

425
00:35:54,031 --> 00:35:56,024
Patrolman James callin' Operations.

426
00:35:57,034 --> 00:36:00,035
This is Patrone.
Did you find that supervisor?

427
00:36:01,205 --> 00:36:04,823
- He's dead, Lieutenant.
- Speak up, will ya? I can't hear ya.

428
00:36:04,958 --> 00:36:09,288
I can't. I'm only 20 yards away
from the hijacked train.

429
00:36:09,421 --> 00:36:12,755
They just shot him with a machine gun.

430
00:36:12,883 --> 00:36:14,923
Is he dead?

431
00:36:15,344 --> 00:36:19,923
- Wouldn't you be, Lieutenant?
- Stay put and keep an eye on things.

432
00:36:20,265 --> 00:36:22,591
Z! They just drew first blood.

433
00:36:22,977 --> 00:36:26,559
That supervisor from Grand Central
Tower. They just killed him.

434
00:36:26,689 --> 00:36:30,140
Oh, my God. Thanks, Rico.

435
00:36:30,276 --> 00:36:33,027
Frank, do you know who went
to 28th from Grand Central?

436
00:36:33,154 --> 00:36:36,772
- Caz Dolowicz. Why?
- Jeez. I knew him.

437
00:36:38,659 --> 00:36:40,782
Hey, whaddaya mean, you knew him?

438
00:36:40,911 --> 00:36:43,200
They just shot him.

439
00:36:43,330 --> 00:36:44,741
Dead?

440
00:36:45,040 --> 00:36:47,875
- Caz? Fat Caz?
- Yeah.

441
00:36:48,294 --> 00:36:50,998
- Garber?
- Aw, shit!

442
00:36:51,672 --> 00:36:54,127
Garber? Are you there, Zach?

443
00:36:56,051 --> 00:36:58,091
- Yeah, who is this?
- Costello.

444
00:36:58,220 --> 00:36:59,134
Yes, Captain.

445
00:36:59,263 --> 00:37:02,679
I'm puttin' you in charge at this end.
I'm goin' to headquarters.

446
00:37:02,808 --> 00:37:05,928
If I don't show up,
the City cops'll hog all the action.

447
00:37:06,062 --> 00:37:08,813
There's one on board the train.
One of the hostages.

448
00:37:08,939 --> 00:37:11,857
You're kiddin'. A cop on the train?
How do you know?

449
00:37:12,109 --> 00:37:16,438
There were two, but one got off at 33rd
and called in later when the news got out.

450
00:37:16,572 --> 00:37:19,145
That means the other one's
still on the train.

451
00:37:19,283 --> 00:37:22,034
- Plainclothes?
- Yeah, Tactical Force.

452
00:37:22,161 --> 00:37:26,158
- Man or woman?
- I never even thought to ask.

453
00:37:26,290 --> 00:37:30,418
Well, doesn't make any difference.
They can't do much single-handed.

454
00:37:31,420 --> 00:37:35,038
Warren, I thought it over.
I know what we're gonna do.

455
00:37:35,174 --> 00:37:36,087
Tell me.

456
00:37:36,217 --> 00:37:39,087
We're gonna let 'em keep
the goddamn subway train.

457
00:37:39,220 --> 00:37:42,007
We got plenty of them.
We'll never even miss it.

458
00:37:42,139 --> 00:37:44,844
How about the 18 hostages?
We gonna miss them?

459
00:37:44,975 --> 00:37:48,973
Warren, goddamnit!
This city hasn't got a million dollars!

460
00:37:49,104 --> 00:37:53,054
Empty one of your Swiss bank accounts.
There's no other way out.

461
00:37:53,192 --> 00:37:55,861
- Don't we get to think about it?
- There's no time.

462
00:37:55,986 --> 00:37:59,402
I still want the full picture.
Get me the police commissioner,

463
00:37:59,531 --> 00:38:03,576
the chairman of the Transit Authority,
and that putz we got for a comptroller.

464
00:38:03,702 --> 00:38:06,703
They're on their way,
but it's no good runnin' to them, Al.

465
00:38:06,831 --> 00:38:09,617
You're the mayor.
The buck stops with you.

466
00:38:09,750 --> 00:38:12,870
- Oh, shit.
- God help us.

467
00:38:13,337 --> 00:38:15,376
Shit! Piss! Fuck!

468
00:38:16,090 --> 00:38:18,794
Call Charlie. Tell him
I'll get to him as soon as I can.

469
00:38:18,926 --> 00:38:20,634
Where's that list on 144?

470
00:38:20,761 --> 00:38:23,169
Command Centre callin'
Pelham One Two Three.

471
00:38:23,305 --> 00:38:25,179
Frank, you're hoggin' my circuits.

472
00:38:25,307 --> 00:38:27,763
I've got motormen callin' me from all over!

473
00:38:27,893 --> 00:38:31,096
Tell 'em to get off the air.
I need some more lines open.

474
00:38:31,230 --> 00:38:35,144
So talkin' to murderers takes priority
over runnin' a railroad?

475
00:38:35,276 --> 00:38:38,395
My only priority is savin'
the lives of these passengers.

476
00:38:38,529 --> 00:38:42,657
Screw the passengers! What do they
expect for 35 cents? To live for ever?

477
00:38:42,783 --> 00:38:44,776
Oh, you're beautiful.

478
00:38:44,910 --> 00:38:48,908
- Do you read me, Pelham?
- I'd go in with guns and blast 'em out!

479
00:38:49,039 --> 00:38:52,989
Why don't you start doin' your work
and let the police do theirs, huh?

480
00:38:53,127 --> 00:38:56,163
Like that cop on the train.
When's he gonna start shootin'?

481
00:38:56,297 --> 00:38:58,123
We don't know if it is a "he".

482
00:38:58,257 --> 00:39:01,127
- Do you read me, Pelham?
- Women cops! What good are they?

483
00:39:01,260 --> 00:39:04,011
Probably can't find her gun
in her goddamn purse!

484
00:39:04,138 --> 00:39:06,593
Pelham One Two Three.
Any news to report?

485
00:39:06,724 --> 00:39:09,393
What's that about news?
Say again about news.

486
00:39:09,518 --> 00:39:12,436
I said have you any news to report?

487
00:39:13,063 --> 00:39:15,471
- No, nothin' yet.
- Atchoo!

488
00:39:16,150 --> 00:39:17,893
Gesundheit!

489
00:39:18,027 --> 00:39:21,312
- What are you calling about?
- Pelham, we need more time.

490
00:39:21,447 --> 00:39:23,486
Shut the door, please.

491
00:39:25,534 --> 00:39:28,868
It is 2.24, Lieutenant.
You've got 49 minutes left.

492
00:39:28,996 --> 00:39:31,534
Be reasonable.
We're tryin' to cooperate,

493
00:39:31,665 --> 00:39:34,951
but we can't do anything
if you don't give us enough time.

494
00:39:35,085 --> 00:39:36,283
49 minutes.

495
00:39:36,420 --> 00:39:39,955
We're dealin' with City Hall. You know
what a mess of red tape that is?

496
00:39:40,090 --> 00:39:41,335
49 minutes.

497
00:39:41,967 --> 00:39:44,505
Look, fella, we know how to tell the time,

498
00:39:44,636 --> 00:39:48,337
but we aren't gonna get any place
if all you do is repeat 49 minutes!

499
00:39:48,474 --> 00:39:50,431
48 minutes.

500
00:39:50,559 --> 00:39:55,138
Yeah, all right, all right.
We'll get back to you as soon as we can.

501
00:39:57,358 --> 00:40:01,402
To hear you plead with that chickenshit
makes me ashamed to be an American!

502
00:40:01,529 --> 00:40:03,320
Go play with your trains.

503
00:40:09,161 --> 00:40:12,530
Stay tuned for an update
on the subway hijacking case.

504
00:40:14,291 --> 00:40:16,498
Get me the borough commander.

505
00:40:16,627 --> 00:40:19,200
- Turn off that goddamn music.
- Yes, sir.

506
00:40:19,338 --> 00:40:22,873
Harry? I'm headin' up to see the mayor.
What's it look like down there?

507
00:40:23,008 --> 00:40:26,543
It's murder, Phil, as usual.
They really smell blood on this one.

508
00:40:26,679 --> 00:40:30,178
- Who's your number two?
- Deputy Chief Inspector Daniels.

509
00:40:30,307 --> 00:40:33,474
He's a good man, Phil.
He handled that protest last month.

510
00:40:33,602 --> 00:40:36,936
- Get those photographers outta here!
- How are you deployed?

511
00:40:37,064 --> 00:40:39,981
50 men inside the tunnel,
north and south of the train,

512
00:40:40,109 --> 00:40:43,809
well concealed, all wearin' vests
and armed with machine guns,

513
00:40:43,946 --> 00:40:47,860
shotguns, handguns, riot guns,
and a half-dozen snipers.

514
00:40:47,991 --> 00:40:50,198
We could fight
the Third World War down there!

515
00:40:50,327 --> 00:40:54,906
Make sure they stay outta sight. If the
hijackers see 'em, we'll have a massacre.

516
00:40:55,040 --> 00:40:58,659
We have a sniper's report that
they're movin' around pretty freely.

517
00:40:58,794 --> 00:41:01,546
The one in the motorman's cab
is an easy shot.

518
00:41:01,672 --> 00:41:06,666
Absolutely no! Understand? We're takin'
the threat seriously! What's upstairs?

519
00:41:06,802 --> 00:41:10,717
Trucks, cars, emergency and
medical units. The works, Phil.

520
00:41:10,848 --> 00:41:13,220
Harry... tell me somethin', will ya?

521
00:41:13,934 --> 00:41:18,845
They're in a tunnel, surrounded on all
sides. How do they expect to get away?

522
00:41:19,398 --> 00:41:21,889
Beats the shit out of me, Phil.

523
00:41:23,861 --> 00:41:28,322
Oh, Al, it's disgustin'.
Would you stop it with the tissue?

524
00:41:28,449 --> 00:41:33,027
Warren, tell him that other mayors have
to live in this house after we're gone.

525
00:41:33,162 --> 00:41:36,531
Go on in there, Al, and I'll send
everybody in. Just sit down.

526
00:41:36,665 --> 00:41:40,034
Thanks for comin' up
on such short notice, fellas.

527
00:41:40,169 --> 00:41:42,208
You all know Jessie, don't you?

528
00:41:43,172 --> 00:41:45,497
Good, Phil, just in time.

529
00:41:46,467 --> 00:41:48,127
A little coffee? Some cake?

530
00:41:48,260 --> 00:41:50,833
Better skip it, Jessie. We're short on time.

531
00:41:50,971 --> 00:41:53,178
We know what's goin' on underground.

532
00:41:53,307 --> 00:41:56,142
The issue is whether or not
we pay the ransom.

533
00:41:56,268 --> 00:41:58,391
Phil? Whaddaya think?

534
00:41:58,520 --> 00:42:03,811
Well, we're fully mobilised. There's
enough firepower to wipe out an army.

535
00:42:03,943 --> 00:42:06,943
But... I can't guarantee
the safety of the hostages.

536
00:42:07,071 --> 00:42:10,771
In other words, you're for
payin' the ransom.

537
00:42:10,908 --> 00:42:13,197
Well, we don't want
another Attica, do we?

538
00:42:13,327 --> 00:42:15,533
- So your vote is?
- I abstain.

539
00:42:15,788 --> 00:42:17,827
Shit! Barney?

540
00:42:18,916 --> 00:42:22,865
The safety of the passengers is
the only concern of the Transit Authority.

541
00:42:23,003 --> 00:42:25,292
- Your vote?
- Pay the two dollars.

542
00:42:25,422 --> 00:42:28,589
If it was two dollars,
I'd pay the two dollars, Barney!

543
00:42:28,717 --> 00:42:32,549
It's a million! A one with six zeros!
Is it comin' outta your pocket?

544
00:42:32,680 --> 00:42:36,547
Come on, will ya save the poor mouth
for later? How do you vote?

545
00:42:36,684 --> 00:42:40,516
- I'm not through discussin' it yet.
- Yes, you are. Now vote.

546
00:42:40,646 --> 00:42:43,267
My concern is with the taxpayers.

547
00:42:43,399 --> 00:42:46,649
I always say millions for defence
but not one cent for tribute.

548
00:42:46,777 --> 00:42:50,526
- Isn't that what I always say?
- Uh-huh. So that's a "no".

549
00:42:50,656 --> 00:42:54,784
All right, Al. You've heard from
the Three Wise Men.

550
00:42:55,661 --> 00:43:00,204
- Now what do you say?
- What are they goin' to say, Warren?

551
00:43:00,624 --> 00:43:02,747
- Who?
- Everybody!

552
00:43:02,876 --> 00:43:06,708
- The press! The man on the street!
- He means the voters.

553
00:43:07,256 --> 00:43:10,839
The Times will support you,
the News will knock you.

554
00:43:10,968 --> 00:43:15,048
The Post will take both sides. The rich'll
support you. Likewise the blacks.

555
00:43:15,180 --> 00:43:18,680
The Puerto Ricans won't give a shit.
So quit stallin'.

556
00:43:18,809 --> 00:43:23,720
Stop bullyin' everybody, Warren!
This is supposed to be a democracy!

557
00:43:23,856 --> 00:43:28,434
Wise up, for Christ sake! We're tryin' to
run a city, not a goddamn democracy!

558
00:43:29,445 --> 00:43:32,114
Al, quit fartin' around! We've gotta pay!

559
00:43:32,823 --> 00:43:34,483
Jessie?

560
00:43:34,616 --> 00:43:36,656
Jessie, what do you say?

561
00:43:36,952 --> 00:43:39,526
A million dollars sounds like
a lot of money.

562
00:43:39,663 --> 00:43:43,032
But just think what
you're gonna get in return.

563
00:43:43,167 --> 00:43:46,037
- What?
- 18 sure votes.

564
00:43:48,172 --> 00:43:50,414
All right. All right. Warren?

565
00:43:51,926 --> 00:43:54,761
- Warren, arrange for the payoff.
- Hallelujah.

566
00:43:54,887 --> 00:43:59,216
Fellas, you heard him. Phil, pass the word
to the bad guys that we're coughin' up.

567
00:43:59,350 --> 00:44:03,098
- What bank do we do business with?
- City National Trust. I'll call.

568
00:44:03,229 --> 00:44:07,855
I'll call. You'll take an hour tryin'
to knock down the interest rate.

569
00:44:10,027 --> 00:44:12,066
Jessie?

570
00:44:12,863 --> 00:44:14,903
I think I handled it all right.

571
00:44:15,991 --> 00:44:18,364
A regular Fiorello La Guardia.

572
00:44:22,748 --> 00:44:26,698
- Patrolman James callin' Operations.
- This is Patrone. What's goin' on?

573
00:44:26,835 --> 00:44:30,002
There's a lot of feet movin' around
out here in the dark.

574
00:44:30,130 --> 00:44:33,084
I figure it's a couple of dozen
sharpshooters and snipers.

575
00:44:33,217 --> 00:44:35,209
- Am I right?
- I wouldn't be surprised.

576
00:44:35,344 --> 00:44:40,931
Make sure they know I'm standin' here
between them and the hijackers.

577
00:44:41,058 --> 00:44:43,300
I'm not all that easy to see in the dark.

578
00:44:49,233 --> 00:44:51,272
Nothin' yet?

579
00:44:51,735 --> 00:44:55,354
Boy! They're sure takin'
their time, aren't they?

580
00:44:55,489 --> 00:45:00,447
- Don't worry. They're gonna have to pay.
- Suppose they don't?

581
00:45:00,577 --> 00:45:03,365
Well, then a lot of people are gonna die.

582
00:45:04,999 --> 00:45:07,038
Includin' us.

583
00:45:07,293 --> 00:45:10,044
Better than selling life insurance, isn't it?

584
00:45:10,171 --> 00:45:13,041
Life insurance? You told me
you were in the army.

585
00:45:13,173 --> 00:45:17,088
I was. That's where I developed
my expensive tastes.

586
00:45:17,219 --> 00:45:20,173
British army. $ 150 a month.
You gotta be kiddin'.

587
00:45:20,306 --> 00:45:22,761
The Africans paid me 5,000.

588
00:45:23,267 --> 00:45:26,802
- A month?
- For leading a battalion.

589
00:45:26,937 --> 00:45:30,021
Jesus! What the hell'd
you get outta that for?

590
00:45:31,692 --> 00:45:33,898
Because the market dried up.

591
00:45:34,028 --> 00:45:36,067
Wow!

592
00:45:36,363 --> 00:45:38,403
5,000!

593
00:45:40,117 --> 00:45:43,201
At least you weren't fired.
But I don't give a shit.

594
00:45:43,329 --> 00:45:46,911
What guy wants to drive a subway train
for the rest of his life?

595
00:45:47,041 --> 00:45:49,496
What did they catch you doing?

596
00:45:50,627 --> 00:45:52,667
Nothin'.

597
00:45:53,088 --> 00:45:56,255
I mean, they framed me.
They needed a fall guy.

598
00:45:56,383 --> 00:46:00,298
Transit cops. Undercover guys.
They got wind of a gang passin' dope.

599
00:46:00,429 --> 00:46:05,091
Transportin' from downtown to uptown,
and givin' it to a motorman.

600
00:46:05,476 --> 00:46:08,927
They tried to pin the evidence on me,
but they didn't find a thing.

601
00:46:09,063 --> 00:46:11,139
You were innocent?

602
00:46:11,273 --> 00:46:15,900
Of course I was innocent.
You think I'd do a thing like that?

603
00:46:19,990 --> 00:46:22,825
I'm on my way to headquarters.
We got the green light.

604
00:46:22,951 --> 00:46:25,822
That's great news.
The men are rarin' to go.

605
00:46:25,955 --> 00:46:30,451
No! We're paying 'em the ransom money.
Pass the word along to the hijackers.

606
00:46:30,584 --> 00:46:32,743
Roger.

607
00:46:32,878 --> 00:46:36,710
Borough Command to the 28th Street
platform. Come in, Daniels.

608
00:46:36,840 --> 00:46:37,872
Daniels.

609
00:46:38,008 --> 00:46:42,421
The mayor's agreed to pay.
Let the hijackers know right away.

610
00:46:42,554 --> 00:46:44,594
Roger.

611
00:46:45,766 --> 00:46:48,138
Command Centre, this is 28th Street.

612
00:46:48,894 --> 00:46:51,350
Do you read me, Command Centre?

613
00:46:51,480 --> 00:46:54,931
- This is Command Centre. Who is this?
- Chief Inspector Daniels.

614
00:46:55,109 --> 00:46:58,774
The mayor's agreed to pay.
Pass it on to the hijackers right away.

615
00:46:58,904 --> 00:47:00,944
Will do, sir.

616
00:47:01,699 --> 00:47:02,730
Pelham One Two Three.

617
00:47:03,158 --> 00:47:05,198
Come in, Pelham One Two Three.

618
00:47:05,786 --> 00:47:07,992
This is Pelham One Two Three.
I read you.

619
00:47:08,831 --> 00:47:12,365
We agree to pay the ransom.
Repeat, we agree to pay...

620
00:47:12,501 --> 00:47:14,909
What? They're gonna do what?

621
00:47:15,045 --> 00:47:16,753
Do you read me, Pelham One Two Three?

622
00:47:16,881 --> 00:47:20,748
- Zach, you're outta your skull.
- I read you, Garber.

623
00:47:20,885 --> 00:47:24,503
Take down my next instructions,
to be followed to the letter.

624
00:47:25,764 --> 00:47:28,765
The money's to be paid
in the following denominations.

625
00:47:28,893 --> 00:47:30,885
500,000 dollars in fifties.

626
00:47:31,020 --> 00:47:33,641
500,000 dollars in hundreds. Right?

627
00:47:34,315 --> 00:47:37,399
500,000 in fifties. 500,000 in hundreds.

628
00:47:37,610 --> 00:47:40,183
Which will be put
in stacks of 200 bills each,

629
00:47:40,321 --> 00:47:42,397
bound with two thick elastic bands.

630
00:47:44,199 --> 00:47:46,572
Two stacks of bills, bound in what?

631
00:47:47,578 --> 00:47:50,283
Bound with thick elastic bands.

632
00:47:50,414 --> 00:47:54,577
All of the bills will be old bills,
their serial numbers to be random.

633
00:47:54,710 --> 00:48:00,084
Now that's all. When the delivery arrives
we'll contact you with further instructions.

634
00:48:00,215 --> 00:48:03,300
- About what? Your getaway?
- Signing off now.

635
00:48:03,427 --> 00:48:05,467
Son of a bitch!

636
00:48:06,430 --> 00:48:11,591
Hey, Pelham. It might interest you to
know I figured out how you're gonna do it.

637
00:48:14,104 --> 00:48:16,975
Yes, it would interest me very much.

638
00:48:17,107 --> 00:48:19,681
You're gonna make everyone
in New York City

639
00:48:19,818 --> 00:48:22,606
close their eyes and count
to a hundred, right?

640
00:48:22,738 --> 00:48:26,783
It is now 2.47. That means
you have got 26 minutes...

641
00:48:26,909 --> 00:48:30,989
Hey, wait a minute, pal. We agreed
to pay the money. Turn your clock off!

642
00:48:31,121 --> 00:48:34,372
- 26 minutes.
- Your instructions were complicated.

643
00:48:34,500 --> 00:48:37,335
The money has to be counted,
stacked, transported.

644
00:48:37,461 --> 00:48:39,750
It just isn't physically possible.

645
00:48:40,631 --> 00:48:43,204
You'd be surprised
what's physically possible.

646
00:48:43,342 --> 00:48:45,382
The clock's running.

647
00:48:46,387 --> 00:48:49,756
26 minutes. After that,
we scratch 'em off one per minute.

648
00:49:02,862 --> 00:49:04,819
Your attention, please!

649
00:49:04,947 --> 00:49:08,530
Ladies and gentlemen,
it might interest you to know

650
00:49:08,659 --> 00:49:11,695
the city of New York has agreed
to pay for your release.

651
00:49:15,541 --> 00:49:18,791
As soon as the money gets here,
will you let us go?

652
00:49:18,919 --> 00:49:20,461
Soon after.

653
00:49:20,588 --> 00:49:25,748
Excuse me, sir. Would you mind
telling us how much you're getting?

654
00:49:25,885 --> 00:49:30,961
- Why is that of interest to you, sir?
- Well, a person likes to know his worth.

655
00:49:31,098 --> 00:49:34,799
- One million dollars.
- That's not so terrific.

656
00:49:36,020 --> 00:49:40,148
FEDERAL RESERVE BANK OF NEW YORK
LOWER MANHATTAN

657
00:50:23,484 --> 00:50:25,726
Pull your pants up, Al.
We're goin' downtown.

658
00:50:25,861 --> 00:50:29,941
- Totally out of the question, Mr LaSalle.
- Nobody asked you.

659
00:50:30,073 --> 00:50:35,115
Warren, for Pete's sake,
I'm sick as a goat. What's the point?

660
00:50:35,246 --> 00:50:39,113
The point, for Pete's sake, is that
the mayor of the city of New York,

661
00:50:39,250 --> 00:50:42,037
trailin' by 22 points in all the polls,

662
00:50:42,169 --> 00:50:44,790
cares enough about
18 citizens in jeopardy

663
00:50:44,922 --> 00:50:47,495
to make a personal appearance
in their behalf.

664
00:50:47,633 --> 00:50:52,295
You know what'll happen?
What always happens. I'll get booed.

665
00:50:52,846 --> 00:50:55,931
- He's a very sick man.
- Will you let go of that!

666
00:50:58,102 --> 00:51:02,265
All you have to do is say a few words
to the hijackers over a bullhorn.

667
00:51:02,397 --> 00:51:04,770
You make a dignified plea for mercy.

668
00:51:04,900 --> 00:51:08,565
Warren, suppose the hijackers
start shootin' at me?

669
00:51:08,779 --> 00:51:11,531
Will you stop!
They have no reason to shoot at you.

670
00:51:11,907 --> 00:51:15,074
Why? Do you think
they're from outta town?

671
00:51:16,370 --> 00:51:18,991
Get dressed, Al. I'll do the jokes.

672
00:51:52,823 --> 00:51:56,773
Garber. Come in, Garber.
Come in, Garber.

673
00:51:57,119 --> 00:51:59,788
- Who are we waitin' for, Z?
- Beats me.

674
00:51:59,997 --> 00:52:02,666
How long's it take to get
all that money together?

675
00:52:02,791 --> 00:52:05,543
We'll never make it.
The passengers are dead ducks.

676
00:52:05,669 --> 00:52:08,077
- I wonder what that cop's thinkin'.
- What cop?

677
00:52:08,213 --> 00:52:11,131
The one who's a hostage.
Shit, I'm glad it's not me.

678
00:52:11,258 --> 00:52:13,832
- Where's that money?
- Make yourself useful.

679
00:52:14,053 --> 00:52:20,008
Get Personnel to get a list of all motormen
discharged durin' the past ten years.

680
00:52:20,142 --> 00:52:24,603
- What are you lookin' for?
- Somebody down there can drive a train.

681
00:52:24,730 --> 00:52:26,438
Tell 'em you want it today.

682
00:52:40,871 --> 00:52:43,872
Mr Grey, can I have a word
with you, please?

683
00:52:43,999 --> 00:52:47,036
Will you stop messing around
with that girl, Mr Grey?

684
00:52:47,169 --> 00:52:49,327
She's a 20-buck-a-trick hooker.

685
00:52:49,463 --> 00:52:52,464
- Who's a 20-buck-a-trick hooker?
- Leave her alone.

686
00:52:52,591 --> 00:52:55,082
Who are you to go around
callin' people "hooker"?!

687
00:52:55,219 --> 00:52:57,970
I can do this job and hump
that broad at the same time.

688
00:52:58,097 --> 00:53:02,426
Listen, you little prick! 20 bucks
wouldn't buy you a good-night kiss!

689
00:53:02,560 --> 00:53:05,430
I'm giving you an order, Mr Grey.

690
00:53:05,562 --> 00:53:07,638
Blow it outta your ass,

691
00:53:07,773 --> 00:53:09,184
Colonel.

692
00:53:09,775 --> 00:53:14,022
You're talkin' to the wrong man.
I'm not your Mr B-B-B-Brown.

693
00:53:14,155 --> 00:53:17,155
I once had a man shot
for talking to me like that.

694
00:53:18,200 --> 00:53:23,787
Well, that's the difference between us.
I've always done my own killin'.

695
00:53:30,838 --> 00:53:32,629
Takin' a hell of a long time.

696
00:53:32,756 --> 00:53:37,418
Think how many times you gotta wet
your thumb to count a million bucks.

697
00:53:51,608 --> 00:53:54,360
Command Centre callin' 28th Street.
Come in, Inspector.

698
00:53:54,486 --> 00:53:55,685
This is Daniels.

699
00:53:55,821 --> 00:53:59,819
- Has the money left yet, Inspector?
- Not yet.

700
00:53:59,950 --> 00:54:03,236
What are they waitin' for?
Give 'em a goose, will ya?

701
00:54:03,370 --> 00:54:05,862
We're runnin' outta time!
We're runnin' outta time!

702
00:54:23,015 --> 00:54:27,476
Pelham One Two Three, this is Command
Centre. Come in, Pelham One Two Three.

703
00:54:28,979 --> 00:54:31,933
- This is Pelham One Two Three.
- This is Garber.

704
00:54:32,066 --> 00:54:36,277
We're movin' a little slowly at this end,
Pelham. We need some more time.

705
00:54:37,029 --> 00:54:38,654
Sorry, no more time.

706
00:54:39,281 --> 00:54:40,941
If you can just see your way...

707
00:54:41,075 --> 00:54:45,950
- Will you hold it down, Frank?
- I want a local sent around the loop...

708
00:54:46,080 --> 00:54:49,199
I said knock it off!
I'm tryin' to buy some time here!

709
00:54:49,333 --> 00:54:51,491
And I'm tryin' to run a railroad!

710
00:54:51,627 --> 00:54:54,996
While you're playin' grab-ass
with a bunch of pirates!

711
00:54:55,130 --> 00:54:58,297
How about 15 more minutes, Pelham?
A lousy 15 minutes?

712
00:54:58,884 --> 00:54:59,915
Negative.

713
00:55:01,470 --> 00:55:05,337
Ten minutes, then. What difference
can ten minutes make to you?

714
00:55:05,474 --> 00:55:07,301
Negative.

715
00:55:11,688 --> 00:55:14,606
- Anythin' wrong?
- Wanted more time.

716
00:55:14,733 --> 00:55:18,862
- How much more?
- Just ten minutes.

717
00:55:18,988 --> 00:55:21,942
- That can't hurt anybody.
- I didn't give it to them.

718
00:55:22,074 --> 00:55:26,285
- Suppose they can't make it?
- Then we do what we said we'd do.

719
00:55:27,830 --> 00:55:31,993
- Maybe an hour isn't enough time.
- You give 'em an hour, they take an hour.

720
00:55:32,126 --> 00:55:36,918
Give 'em two hours, they take two hours.
An hour is plenty of time, Mr Green.

721
00:55:37,047 --> 00:55:39,503
Yeah, but supposin' it isn't?

722
00:55:45,305 --> 00:55:49,849
This is the borough commander.
Come in, Headquarters Charlie!

723
00:55:50,394 --> 00:55:54,226
Aren't you guys movin' yet?
Do you know what the damn time is?

724
00:55:54,356 --> 00:55:56,847
We're still waitin' for the money, sir.

725
00:55:56,984 --> 00:56:01,147
If I don't see your faces before the
deadline, I don't wanna see them at all!

726
00:56:01,280 --> 00:56:03,687
- Everl
- Yes, sir.

727
00:56:03,824 --> 00:56:06,280
I told you. It's gonna be our ass.

728
00:56:11,832 --> 00:56:15,497
- This is a million dollars?
- It's what it buys. Not what it weighs.

729
00:57:02,132 --> 00:57:04,802
Eight minutes. We're not gonna make it.

730
00:57:11,517 --> 00:57:16,642
- Inspector, where are they now, please?
- Centre Street, just north of Chambers.

731
00:57:16,772 --> 00:57:19,773
That gives us seven minutes.
Not enough time, sir.

732
00:57:19,900 --> 00:57:24,313
Even if they get to 28th Street on time,
we still gotta carry it down track on foot.

733
00:57:24,447 --> 00:57:26,486
No way, sir.

734
00:57:31,245 --> 00:57:34,365
Look, we're scarin' the shit
outta everybody.

735
00:57:34,498 --> 00:57:36,538
Yeah, includin' me.

736
00:57:43,090 --> 00:57:46,791
Pelham One Two Three, this is Garber.
Come in, Pelham One Two Three.

737
00:57:46,927 --> 00:57:49,383
Garber, this is Pelham One Two Three.

738
00:57:49,513 --> 00:57:54,720
The money's en route, makin' pretty good
time too, but it won't get to you by 3.13.

739
00:57:54,852 --> 00:57:56,975
I'm very sorry to hear that.

740
00:57:57,104 --> 00:57:59,311
Suppose we get it to the entrance by then.

741
00:57:59,440 --> 00:58:03,484
Will you change your deadline from
delivery to you to arrival at 28th Street?

742
00:58:03,611 --> 00:58:09,364
Would you do that at least? Do you
read me, Pelham, for cryin' out loud?

743
00:58:12,620 --> 00:58:15,989
All right, Garber.
But no more concessions.

744
00:58:16,165 --> 00:58:19,949
- Is that quite clear?
- Quite clear. Quite clear.

745
00:58:20,878 --> 00:58:25,207
They bought it. If we get the money
to the station by 3.13 we'll be OK.

746
00:58:25,341 --> 00:58:26,503
Good work, Garber.

747
00:58:26,801 --> 00:58:30,632
Headquarters Charlie,
headin' north on Centre Street...

748
00:58:30,846 --> 00:58:32,720
You've got four minutes!

749
00:58:32,848 --> 00:58:35,517
Yes, sir, we'll make it...
We'll never make it.

750
00:58:35,643 --> 00:58:37,682
Sir, the mayor is on his way down.

751
00:58:37,811 --> 00:58:39,934
We'll hold the crowd till he gets here.

752
00:59:09,093 --> 00:59:11,132
Mr Green.

753
00:59:11,512 --> 00:59:12,508
Yes.

754
00:59:13,514 --> 00:59:15,969
Coming up in one minute.

755
00:59:24,483 --> 00:59:27,104
Have you decided which one
it's gonna be?

756
00:59:27,236 --> 00:59:29,478
Does that make any difference?

757
00:59:31,740 --> 00:59:33,780
I guess not.

758
00:59:40,916 --> 00:59:45,459
OK. 50 seconds and then
I'm gonna eliminate one.

759
00:59:48,841 --> 00:59:53,135
Headquarters Charlie,
approachin' Astor Place.

760
00:59:53,262 --> 00:59:57,306
You've still got 28 blocks!
Floor the son of a bitch!

761
01:00:08,861 --> 01:00:11,897
Whaddaya mean, it's been wrecked?
We're outta time!

762
01:00:12,031 --> 01:00:15,731
I know we're outta time.
Couldn't make it, that's all.

763
01:00:15,868 --> 01:00:19,071
That's all? They're about
to shoot an innocent person!

764
01:00:19,204 --> 01:00:23,119
If they know the truck is wrecked,
how can they expect us to be on time?

765
01:00:23,250 --> 01:00:26,915
They don't know anythin' down there.
How can they know anythin'...

766
01:00:27,046 --> 01:00:29,085
Holy mackerel, that's it.

767
01:00:29,465 --> 01:00:34,127
Pelham One Two Three, the money has
arrived. Repeat, the money has arrived.

768
01:00:34,720 --> 01:00:38,848
Do you read me, Pelham One Two Three?
The money has arrived.

769
01:00:40,059 --> 01:00:44,555
This is Pelham One Two Three.
You made it just in time, didn't you?

770
01:00:56,241 --> 01:00:58,697
Get it up there! Move!

771
01:01:03,207 --> 01:01:05,081
I hope it works.

772
01:01:11,799 --> 01:01:13,838
Are you still there, Garber?

773
01:01:15,386 --> 01:01:18,505
Still here. Tell me somethin', Pelham.

774
01:01:18,639 --> 01:01:22,222
If we were a second late, you would've
knocked off an innocent party?

775
01:01:22,351 --> 01:01:26,218
Affirmative. Now the instructions
for the delivery of the money.

776
01:01:26,355 --> 01:01:29,391
As usual, you'll follow them
to the letter, OK?

777
01:01:29,525 --> 01:01:31,564
I got it. Go ahead.

778
01:01:32,278 --> 01:01:34,021
Two unarmed policemen...

779
01:01:34,155 --> 01:01:35,103
Atchoo!

780
01:01:35,614 --> 01:01:37,690
Gesundheit.

781
01:01:37,825 --> 01:01:40,779
Two unarmed policemen
will walk down the track.

782
01:01:40,911 --> 01:01:43,117
One with the money,
the other with a torch,

783
01:01:43,247 --> 01:01:46,283
which he will flash continuously
from side to side.

784
01:01:46,875 --> 01:01:49,912
When they reach the car,
the rear door will be opened

785
01:01:50,045 --> 01:01:52,999
and the one with the money
will throw it onto the train.

786
01:01:53,132 --> 01:01:57,877
Then they will both turn and walk back
to 28th Street station. Acknowledge.

787
01:01:58,011 --> 01:02:00,419
- I got it. Is that all?
- That's all for now.

788
01:02:00,556 --> 01:02:04,007
But keep in mind, won't you,
that the same ground rules apply.

789
01:02:04,143 --> 01:02:07,927
Any wrong move by anyone
and I kill a hostage.

790
01:02:08,063 --> 01:02:09,807
Coulda guessed that part.

791
01:02:09,940 --> 01:02:12,894
You have got five minutes
to deliver this money.

792
01:02:13,277 --> 01:02:15,649
You don't think
you're gonna get out, do ya?

793
01:02:15,821 --> 01:02:17,944
It's now 3.14.

794
01:02:18,449 --> 01:02:20,156
You've got till 3.19.

795
01:02:20,284 --> 01:02:21,695
Over.

796
01:02:22,620 --> 01:02:24,529
Over. Bastard.

797
01:02:33,047 --> 01:02:34,920
About fuckin' time!

798
01:02:35,049 --> 01:02:37,504
You two! Get the money outta there!

799
01:02:37,635 --> 01:02:40,920
Which one has the flashlight?
Then you carry the money.

800
01:02:41,055 --> 01:02:43,427
Gimme that paper.
You've got four minutes!

801
01:02:43,557 --> 01:02:46,593
Never mind the goddamn salutes!
Just get goin'!

802
01:02:55,820 --> 01:02:58,192
Jesus, it's the goddamn mayor.

803
01:03:01,492 --> 01:03:04,861
- You get the feelin' we ain't alone?
- Whaddaya mean?

804
01:03:09,125 --> 01:03:14,119
We got four sub-machine-guns in front
of us, and all these jokers behind us.

805
01:03:14,255 --> 01:03:17,624
I feel like I'm walkin' into
the fuckin' OK Corral.

806
01:03:22,388 --> 01:03:24,427
Pow!

807
01:03:24,723 --> 01:03:26,763
Shit!

808
01:04:08,892 --> 01:04:11,099
Hold your fire, goddamnit!

809
01:04:11,228 --> 01:04:13,185
Quiet!

810
01:04:21,364 --> 01:04:25,231
- Are you all right?
- Yeah. It's not too b-b-bad.

811
01:04:25,367 --> 01:04:28,819
- I think it went right through.
- Move back, come on. Move back.

812
01:04:28,954 --> 01:04:31,908
Give me that scarf. Give me that scarf!

813
01:04:32,041 --> 01:04:33,867
Keep quiet!

814
01:04:34,001 --> 01:04:37,833
- OK?
- Yeah. I don't feel p-pain too much.

815
01:04:38,547 --> 01:04:40,836
- How many shots?
- Just one.

816
01:04:40,966 --> 01:04:45,296
The rest was me and then they answered.
I didn't see anybody, I just got mad.

817
01:04:45,429 --> 01:04:46,804
Goddamnit!

818
01:04:46,930 --> 01:04:48,389
Mr Grey?

819
01:04:52,019 --> 01:04:55,222
You don't think they're finished
out there, do ya?

820
01:04:55,355 --> 01:04:59,056
Go back there and help Mr Green,
will you, please?

821
01:05:00,653 --> 01:05:03,737
Some girl-scout
chickenshit outfit I'm in here.

822
01:05:06,909 --> 01:05:10,657
I suppose somebody out there
got nervous or bored.

823
01:05:10,788 --> 01:05:12,827
Been there a long time.

824
01:05:13,832 --> 01:05:15,706
Can't afford to let it pass.

825
01:05:19,546 --> 01:05:22,334
Who started it?
Who fired first? Them or us?

826
01:05:22,466 --> 01:05:26,843
I don't know, Lieutenant. It came from
somewhere behind me in the dark.

827
01:05:26,971 --> 01:05:29,177
It had to be one of the snipers.

828
01:05:29,306 --> 01:05:33,304
Somebody just took it in his head
to fire on his own? How could he?

829
01:05:33,435 --> 01:05:35,677
Easy, Lieutenant.

830
01:05:35,813 --> 01:05:37,521
Real easy.

831
01:05:37,648 --> 01:05:40,851
Can you see what's goin' on
inside the train?

832
01:05:41,443 --> 01:05:44,610
No, not too good.
I'd sure hate to be in there findin' out.

833
01:05:56,417 --> 01:05:58,456
Conductor.

834
01:06:02,423 --> 01:06:05,922
- You mean me?
- Yes. Stand up and come down here.

835
01:06:06,385 --> 01:06:09,172
- Why, what are you gonna do?
- You can help me.

836
01:06:09,304 --> 01:06:13,931
- Come on. Come down here.
- Look, if he doesn't wanna go...

837
01:06:14,059 --> 01:06:18,602
All right, everybody. Just get back
on your seats. Very quietly.

838
01:06:19,523 --> 01:06:21,729
Come on. Back on your seats.

839
01:06:21,859 --> 01:06:25,773
All right, conductor. I want you to
walk up track about a hundred feet.

840
01:06:25,905 --> 01:06:29,605
Just wait for the men delivering
the money, all right?

841
01:06:29,742 --> 01:06:31,781
I'll open the door for you.

842
01:06:33,788 --> 01:06:36,160
Why do I have to go?

843
01:06:40,544 --> 01:06:43,664
Come on. Please go.
There's nothing to worry about.

844
01:06:46,801 --> 01:06:49,338
Look! Somebody's climbin' down!

845
01:06:56,018 --> 01:06:58,260
Christ, he's comin' this way!

846
01:07:02,858 --> 01:07:04,400
Oh, no!

847
01:07:14,203 --> 01:07:15,317
What?

848
01:07:15,454 --> 01:07:19,368
Why would they shoot a hostage?
We're still under the deadline.

849
01:07:19,500 --> 01:07:22,500
- Somebody threw a shot at them.
- Who the hell was it?

850
01:07:22,628 --> 01:07:25,036
Nobody knows. My bet is we never will.

851
01:07:25,172 --> 01:07:28,208
Z, when are we gonna hear
from that cop who's on board?

852
01:07:28,342 --> 01:07:32,292
What do you want, Rico? A suicide?
There's heavily armed men down there.

853
01:07:32,429 --> 01:07:36,593
What chance has one lousy cop got,
especially if it's a dame?

854
01:07:37,393 --> 01:07:39,432
Boy, what a mess!

855
01:07:42,815 --> 01:07:45,981
Pelham One Two Three, come in.
This is Garber.

856
01:07:46,110 --> 01:07:48,565
Here is Pelham One Two Three.
Come in, Garber.

857
01:07:48,696 --> 01:07:51,566
For Christ's sake, fella,
did ya have to do it?

858
01:07:51,699 --> 01:07:54,949
One of my men was fired at.
I warned you what the penalty would be.

859
01:07:55,077 --> 01:07:57,912
- Yeah, you warned me.
- Where's the money?

860
01:07:59,415 --> 01:08:02,202
I'm going to give you 30 seconds more.

861
01:08:11,635 --> 01:08:13,177
Hey, you guys!

862
01:08:13,304 --> 01:08:17,764
- Christ, who's that?
- Transit cop. I got orders for you.

863
01:08:17,892 --> 01:08:20,513
Resume delivery on the double.

864
01:08:20,645 --> 01:08:23,895
I don't suppose we could
have that in writin'?

865
01:08:31,989 --> 01:08:34,444
Mr Blue, we got a light!

866
01:08:49,673 --> 01:08:52,757
All right. Open the door,
would you, Mr Brown?

867
01:08:53,469 --> 01:08:57,169
All right, gentlemen.
Hands in evidence, please.

868
01:08:57,389 --> 01:08:59,429
Put up your hands!

869
01:09:02,978 --> 01:09:05,766
All right. Throw the money up here.

870
01:09:06,774 --> 01:09:08,813
Into the cab.

871
01:09:08,942 --> 01:09:10,982
Push it up.

872
01:09:11,654 --> 01:09:14,654
Thank you. Now turn around.

873
01:09:16,533 --> 01:09:20,911
Go home to your wives and children.
Keep the hands up. Take it very easily.

874
01:09:21,372 --> 01:09:23,910
Shut the door, Mr Brown, will you?

875
01:09:41,517 --> 01:09:43,556
Mr Grey.

876
01:09:44,437 --> 01:09:46,476
Jesus H Christ!

877
01:09:49,900 --> 01:09:52,272
I've never seen a million dollars before.

878
01:09:52,403 --> 01:09:55,072
You can load up first, Mr Grey.

879
01:09:58,242 --> 01:10:00,318
I'll talk to Garber.

880
01:10:00,453 --> 01:10:02,990
All that money! I can't believe it!

881
01:10:03,539 --> 01:10:05,615
I'm gonna die today.

882
01:10:05,749 --> 01:10:08,620
Well... either you live or you die.

883
01:10:10,462 --> 01:10:13,463
- That's 18 packs each, right?
- Right.

884
01:10:28,272 --> 01:10:31,392
This is Pelham One Two Three.
Do you read me, Garber?

885
01:10:31,525 --> 01:10:35,570
- This is Garber. Go ahead.
- I'm gonna give you three instructions.

886
01:10:35,696 --> 01:10:38,448
Each one is to be followed precisely.
Is that clear?

887
01:10:38,574 --> 01:10:40,033
So far.

888
01:10:40,367 --> 01:10:46,121
1) At the end of this conversation, you
will restore power to the entire sector.

889
01:10:47,083 --> 01:10:48,660
Right. Restore power.

890
01:10:49,668 --> 01:10:53,915
2) You will clear the local track all the
way from 28th Street to South Ferry.

891
01:10:54,047 --> 01:10:57,713
By clear I mean switches properly set,
all signals green.

892
01:10:57,843 --> 01:10:59,634
I emphasise green, Garber.

893
01:10:59,762 --> 01:11:03,095
If I so much as see a red light,
let alone get tripped by one,

894
01:11:03,224 --> 01:11:05,299
I'll shoot another hostage.

895
01:11:14,777 --> 01:11:17,398
You will also remove all police
from the tunnel.

896
01:11:17,530 --> 01:11:20,199
If I see a policeman
between here and South Ferry,

897
01:11:20,616 --> 01:11:24,779
I'll shoot another hostage.
Any deviation, I'll shoot another hostage.

898
01:11:24,912 --> 01:11:29,906
Listen, fella, after this is over
you should seek out psychiatric help.

899
01:11:30,501 --> 01:11:35,246
Let me know when all my points have
been complied with. Over and out.

900
01:11:37,216 --> 01:11:40,086
- Rico, are you there?
- I'm here, Z. What's up?

901
01:11:40,219 --> 01:11:42,674
Hold on while I cut in the City cops.

902
01:11:43,431 --> 01:11:45,968
Frank, hook me up and get outta there.

903
01:11:47,393 --> 01:11:49,432
What a way to run a railroad!

904
01:11:51,438 --> 01:11:54,143
- Inspector Daniels. This is Garber.
- This is Daniels.

905
01:11:54,483 --> 01:11:58,433
Inspector, I have Lieutenant Patrone
of the Transit Police on the line.

906
01:11:58,571 --> 01:12:03,232
The hijackers want power restored,
all tracks cleared,

907
01:12:03,575 --> 01:12:07,276
signals green to South Ferry,
and no cops anywhere in sight.

908
01:12:07,413 --> 01:12:11,411
OK, sir, so we go along with that.
We have to. But then what?

909
01:12:11,542 --> 01:12:14,033
- What do you think they got in mind?
- Beats me, Z.

910
01:12:14,169 --> 01:12:16,661
I wouldn't have picked a tunnel
for a getaway.

911
01:12:16,881 --> 01:12:18,505
But they did pick it.

912
01:12:18,632 --> 01:12:23,211
And since everythin' they've done has
been worked out to the smallest detail,

913
01:12:23,345 --> 01:12:25,967
it stands to reason
they got the rest worked out.

914
01:12:26,098 --> 01:12:29,265
Power restored and track cleared.
But why South Ferry?

915
01:12:29,393 --> 01:12:34,731
Well, do you think it's the water, Rico?
Maybe they got a boat in the harbour.

916
01:12:34,982 --> 01:12:39,857
We'd better play it one step at a time.
Garber, you see about restorin' the power.

917
01:12:39,987 --> 01:12:42,941
I'll start pullin' our units out of the tunnel.

918
01:12:43,073 --> 01:12:47,451
We can follow them on the street.
Except how do we know where they'll be?

919
01:12:47,578 --> 01:12:50,329
Grand Central Tower
has 'em on their board.

920
01:12:50,456 --> 01:12:54,239
They stop any place before South Ferry,
we know about it.

921
01:12:54,501 --> 01:12:56,209
I'll check in when I get to my car.

922
01:12:56,837 --> 01:12:59,672
I just figured out how
they're gonna get away.

923
01:12:59,798 --> 01:13:03,084
- I'm listenin'.
- They're gonna fly the train to Cuba.

924
01:13:05,429 --> 01:13:07,137
You're a sick man, Rico.

925
01:13:07,264 --> 01:13:11,476
Whaddaya want me to do?
The power's still off! Move 'em by bus!

926
01:13:11,602 --> 01:13:14,556
You haven't got any buses?
Go out and hijack some!

927
01:13:14,688 --> 01:13:18,935
Hey, Garber, what's goin' on?
Do I get my trains back now or don't I?

928
01:13:19,067 --> 01:13:20,775
You don't. Not yet.

929
01:13:20,903 --> 01:13:23,857
Do you realise the goddamn
rush hour starts in an hour?

930
01:13:23,989 --> 01:13:27,405
Will you shut up and listen?
I got a new set of instructions.

931
01:13:27,534 --> 01:13:33,655
Your fuckin' instructions! I'm not liftin' a
finger to help the killers of Caz Dolowicz.

932
01:13:37,920 --> 01:13:39,165
Hey!

933
01:13:39,296 --> 01:13:42,297
Now you listen to me,
you dumb son of a bitch.

934
01:13:42,424 --> 01:13:46,718
If you don't do what I say, you'll be havin'
dinner tonight with Caz Dolowicz!

935
01:13:46,845 --> 01:13:48,885
Jesus Christ, what are you...!

936
01:13:56,313 --> 01:13:57,808
OK.

937
01:13:58,607 --> 01:14:00,646
Better take the case out.

938
01:14:07,283 --> 01:14:10,698
All right, ladies and gentlemen.
Pay attention, please.

939
01:14:10,828 --> 01:14:12,904
In a while we hope to be moving again.

940
01:14:13,039 --> 01:14:16,205
Then, with a bit of luck,
you'll be released unharmed.

941
01:14:16,333 --> 01:14:20,283
Until then, of course,
you'll continue to obey my orders.

942
01:14:20,421 --> 01:14:22,460
Thank you for your cooperation.

943
01:14:22,590 --> 01:14:24,629
Hey, dude.

944
01:14:25,718 --> 01:14:29,964
As you're goin' downtown anyway, you
mind droppin' me off at Fulton Street?

945
01:14:30,389 --> 01:14:33,390
You're a wise mother, you know that?
Like some more?

946
01:14:35,352 --> 01:14:38,686
This'll give 'em a jolt,
even before they expected it.

947
01:14:39,022 --> 01:14:41,561
- Look at this.
- Holy Christ, she's movin'.

948
01:14:41,692 --> 01:14:45,144
They promised to wait until
we cleared track all the way down.

949
01:14:45,279 --> 01:14:47,318
Jenkins, get Command Centre.

950
01:14:47,906 --> 01:14:50,195
Grand Central Tower,
callin' Command Centre.

951
01:14:50,325 --> 01:14:53,077
- Command Centre.
- She's movin'.

952
01:14:53,204 --> 01:14:55,576
- Who's movin'?
- Pelham One Two Three.

953
01:14:55,706 --> 01:14:57,746
What? Since when?

954
01:14:57,875 --> 01:14:59,250
Just started.

955
01:14:59,376 --> 01:15:01,749
Hold on. I'll put ya on a tie-in.

956
01:15:02,796 --> 01:15:04,836
Rico, she's movin'.

957
01:15:06,342 --> 01:15:08,915
- Who's movin'?
- Who do ya think? Pelham.

958
01:15:09,303 --> 01:15:13,217
- It's too soon. We're not set up yet.
- You heard from Daniels yet?

959
01:15:13,349 --> 01:15:15,590
He's in a squad car
on Park Avenue South.

960
01:15:16,852 --> 01:15:19,936
- Inspector? She's movin', sir.
- Who's movin'?

961
01:15:21,273 --> 01:15:24,606
What's the matter with everybody?
How many hijacked trains we got?

962
01:15:25,027 --> 01:15:28,775
They're not supposed to do that yet.
How far have they gone?

963
01:15:28,906 --> 01:15:33,283
- Grand Central? How far have they gone?
- Comin' up on 23rd Street.

964
01:15:33,619 --> 01:15:38,245
- Better move those cops off the platform.
- Better follow along down Park Avenue.

965
01:15:38,374 --> 01:15:39,702
Get me 23rd Street.

966
01:15:39,833 --> 01:15:41,743
Comin' in to 23rd Street.

967
01:15:41,877 --> 01:15:44,665
All right. Steady as she goes now.

968
01:16:04,441 --> 01:16:10,610
Garber? Just had a terrible thought. What
if they set the throttle and jumped off?

969
01:16:10,739 --> 01:16:14,653
While we're chasin' the train, they're
sneakin' out somewhere behind us.

970
01:16:14,785 --> 01:16:17,490
Ingenious, sir, except it's impossible.

971
01:16:17,621 --> 01:16:21,785
- Why?
- A gizmo known as a deadman's feature.

972
01:16:21,917 --> 01:16:25,785
It's built into the control handle
in case the motorman drops dead.

973
01:16:25,921 --> 01:16:30,500
The handle has to have a man's hand
pressin' down on it, hard, at all times.

974
01:16:30,634 --> 01:16:33,339
Otherwise it don't work.
The train stops cold.

975
01:16:33,471 --> 01:16:34,846
I see.

976
01:16:34,972 --> 01:16:39,800
Nice try, though. I'll give 'em a call
in case you're still worried about it.

977
01:16:40,269 --> 01:16:43,852
Pelham One Two Three,
what's goin' on down there?

978
01:16:43,980 --> 01:16:46,852
The tracks aren't cleared yet.
How come you're movin'?

979
01:16:46,984 --> 01:16:49,439
We're trying to put some
distance between us

980
01:16:49,570 --> 01:16:53,104
and all those policemen
you've got hidden back there.

981
01:16:53,240 --> 01:16:55,647
You're gonna run into a lot of red signals.

982
01:16:55,785 --> 01:16:59,319
- I don't want you to blame us for it.
- I won't blame you for anything.

983
01:16:59,455 --> 01:17:03,287
Just let us know when you've
cleared the track. OK, signing off.

984
01:17:03,458 --> 01:17:09,082
Do you think he's able to figure anythin'
out? I mean, all those questions.

985
01:17:09,214 --> 01:17:12,299
Not surprising under
the circumstances, is it?

986
01:17:13,135 --> 01:17:15,590
They're thinking what
we want them to think.

987
01:17:15,721 --> 01:17:17,927
Ah, there it is.

988
01:17:18,057 --> 01:17:21,508
OK. Stop a few yards past it, will you?

989
01:17:21,644 --> 01:17:23,683
All right.

990
01:17:27,483 --> 01:17:29,107
Thank you, Mr Green.

991
01:17:32,488 --> 01:17:35,157
He shut down again. Pass it along.

992
01:17:35,282 --> 01:17:39,991
Grand Central Tower callin' Command
Centre. Come in, Command Centre.

993
01:17:40,121 --> 01:17:41,151
Command Centre.

994
01:17:41,288 --> 01:17:44,788
She stopped again, Lieutenant.
Below 18th Street station.

995
01:17:44,916 --> 01:17:46,956
Got ya. Thanks.

996
01:17:47,586 --> 01:17:50,041
Inspector, they stopped again.
Where are you?

997
01:17:50,172 --> 01:17:53,541
- Approachin' 17th Street.
- Pull over. You're right above them.

998
01:17:53,676 --> 01:17:55,502
And then what?

999
01:17:55,636 --> 01:17:58,209
It's up to them. I'll get back to you, sir.

1000
01:18:08,774 --> 01:18:13,151
Pelham One Two Three. Callin' Pelham
One Two Three. Come in, please.

1001
01:18:14,989 --> 01:18:19,698
Pelham One Two Three, Pelham One Two
Three, this is Command Centre. Come in.

1002
01:18:19,827 --> 01:18:21,866
Quick as you can.

1003
01:18:22,538 --> 01:18:25,788
Pelham One Two Three.
This is Garber. Come in, please.

1004
01:18:25,916 --> 01:18:27,956
Come in, please.

1005
01:18:29,920 --> 01:18:32,541
What the hell's goin' on out there?

1006
01:18:32,673 --> 01:18:34,464
Who s-s-said you could talk?

1007
01:18:37,428 --> 01:18:42,588
Pelham One Two Three, come in. Pelham
One Two Three, why don't you answer?

1008
01:18:44,059 --> 01:18:46,550
Frank, how long before
the track's cleared?

1009
01:18:46,687 --> 01:18:50,554
You mean before this railroad is so fucked
it'll take a computer to put it back?

1010
01:18:50,691 --> 01:18:53,479
Yes, Frank, that's what I meant.

1011
01:18:53,611 --> 01:18:57,311
About five or six minutes.
I got a snag at Brooklyn Bridge.

1012
01:18:58,365 --> 01:19:02,114
- There's somethin' goin' on down there.
- Whaddaya think?

1013
01:19:02,244 --> 01:19:04,486
I don't have the slightest idea.

1014
01:19:05,331 --> 01:19:08,996
Rico, I don't care what those clowns said,
I want men on every...

1015
01:19:09,126 --> 01:19:11,333
Wait a minute. Hold on a second.

1016
01:19:11,461 --> 01:19:12,493
Inspector Daniels?

1017
01:19:12,629 --> 01:19:16,757
I think we need officers on every platform
from 14th Street to South Ferry.

1018
01:19:16,884 --> 01:19:18,923
Good idea, Lieutenant. Will do.

1019
01:19:19,053 --> 01:19:21,722
I'll come up to 17th Street and join ya.

1020
01:19:23,140 --> 01:19:25,631
Rico, how about that list of motormen?

1021
01:19:25,768 --> 01:19:28,306
They're workin' on it. I told 'em to rush it.

1022
01:19:28,437 --> 01:19:32,814
Come up here and take over the radio for
me. But don't tell 'em the track's clear.

1023
01:19:32,941 --> 01:19:35,646
I don't want them startin' again
until I get there.

1024
01:19:35,778 --> 01:19:37,153
Will do, Z.

1025
01:20:26,912 --> 01:20:30,115
- Inspector Daniels?
- Daniels.

1026
01:20:30,249 --> 01:20:33,950
Oh, l, uh... I thought you were a, uh...
like a shorter guy.

1027
01:20:34,086 --> 01:20:36,375
I don't know what I thought.

1028
01:20:37,047 --> 01:20:39,834
- Anythin' happenin'?
- They're still down there.

1029
01:20:39,967 --> 01:20:42,921
If this street collapsed,
we'd land right on top of 'em.

1030
01:20:43,053 --> 01:20:45,544
Command Centre to DCl, Manhattan.

1031
01:20:46,807 --> 01:20:48,598
Yeah, Rico, this is Garber.

1032
01:20:48,726 --> 01:20:52,344
Track's been cleared for two minutes.
Should I call the hijackers?

1033
01:20:52,479 --> 01:20:57,022
Yeah, let 'em know. And let us know
when they start movin', will ya?

1034
01:20:57,151 --> 01:21:01,397
What do we do? If they pick up speed
on us we'll have trouble keepin' up.

1035
01:21:01,530 --> 01:21:04,697
I think we oughta take off.
Get a jump on them for a change.

1036
01:21:04,825 --> 01:21:09,736
Move it. Tell the sergeant to hold
the men here until further word.

1037
01:21:09,872 --> 01:21:11,911
Yes, sir.

1038
01:21:16,003 --> 01:21:17,248
Fits like a glove.

1039
01:21:17,379 --> 01:21:21,163
- Is it gonna come away clean?
- It's gonna work all right.

1040
01:21:21,300 --> 01:21:23,791
Command Centre to
Pelham One Two Three.

1041
01:21:23,927 --> 01:21:26,597
- Who's that?
- Give me the mike.

1042
01:21:29,641 --> 01:21:32,761
- Here.
- This is Pelham.

1043
01:21:32,895 --> 01:21:36,430
- What happened to Garber?
- Even great men have to pee.

1044
01:21:37,024 --> 01:21:39,941
The track's cleared
all the way to South Ferry.

1045
01:21:40,068 --> 01:21:42,904
Thank you.
Give the lieutenant my regards.

1046
01:21:43,364 --> 01:21:46,649
- Do it yourself, at the arraignment.
- Over and out.

1047
01:21:46,784 --> 01:21:48,492
Best get going.

1048
01:21:48,619 --> 01:21:50,658
All right, Mr Brown.

1049
01:21:59,505 --> 01:22:03,668
You will all remain seated.
That means nobody is to get up.

1050
01:22:06,136 --> 01:22:07,595
OK.

1051
01:22:14,562 --> 01:22:17,313
- Now what?
- Me you're askin'?

1052
01:22:40,170 --> 01:22:42,210
OK. Come on.

1053
01:22:46,218 --> 01:22:48,424
Hey, where are you goin'?!

1054
01:22:48,554 --> 01:22:50,842
I'm a police officer!

1055
01:22:54,810 --> 01:22:57,764
- Mr Blue?
- Yeah, what do you want?

1056
01:22:57,896 --> 01:23:01,846
- I thought I saw somethin' f-f-fall off.
- What do you mean, something?

1057
01:23:01,984 --> 01:23:06,646
- Might've been a person. I ain't sure.
- All right, let's make sure.

1058
01:23:07,490 --> 01:23:10,609
We haven't got time.
Get back up here. Come on.

1059
01:23:19,126 --> 01:23:22,744
Command Centre,
Pelham One Two Three's in motion!

1060
01:23:39,855 --> 01:23:42,228
Where do you think
they're takin' us now?!

1061
01:23:42,357 --> 01:23:46,355
- Don't worry, they're gonna let us all go!
- How do you know that?!

1062
01:23:46,487 --> 01:23:48,978
They got the money!
They got what they want!

1063
01:23:53,327 --> 01:23:56,743
Wait a minute! Wait a minute!
Can't anybody count?

1064
01:23:57,415 --> 01:23:59,952
They all four got off!

1065
01:24:00,500 --> 01:24:04,368
There's nobody drivin' the fuckin' train!

1066
01:24:11,053 --> 01:24:13,509
Anybody in there?!

1067
01:24:22,356 --> 01:24:24,147
All right, all clear.

1068
01:24:24,274 --> 01:24:27,228
All right, then. You know the drill.

1069
01:24:27,361 --> 01:24:30,564
We do it by the numbers. Hats.

1070
01:24:33,951 --> 01:24:36,358
- Glasses.
- Drills and numbers...

1071
01:24:36,495 --> 01:24:39,449
This is all chickenshit.
Why don't we just do it?

1072
01:24:39,582 --> 01:24:41,621
Moustaches.

1073
01:24:54,346 --> 01:24:57,016
All right, reverse coats.

1074
01:25:08,027 --> 01:25:12,653
Pelham One Two Three's between Astor
Place and Bleecker. Speed's increasin'.

1075
01:25:13,073 --> 01:25:16,857
Pelham One Two Three now between
Astor Place and Bleecker.

1076
01:25:17,286 --> 01:25:22,625
Doesn't make any sense. They know
we're monitorin' their position.

1077
01:25:22,750 --> 01:25:24,410
- So?
- So it's dumb.

1078
01:25:24,543 --> 01:25:26,251
Who said crooks were smart?

1079
01:25:26,378 --> 01:25:30,708
But these have been smart.
We're overlookin' somethin', Inspector.

1080
01:25:31,258 --> 01:25:33,298
OK. New hats.

1081
01:25:43,354 --> 01:25:46,058
OK. Magazines in pockets.

1082
01:25:50,611 --> 01:25:54,479
- I never knew these things went so fast!
- We're gonna be killed!

1083
01:25:54,782 --> 01:25:59,491
- Stop it! Nobody's gonna get killed!
- A hell of a lot you know, old man!

1084
01:25:59,620 --> 01:26:03,783
But I do know! I've been ridin' the
subways since before you were born!

1085
01:26:03,916 --> 01:26:09,337
I'm an expert. You see, they have
something called stoppers,

1086
01:26:09,463 --> 01:26:11,789
or stickers, or something like that.

1087
01:26:11,924 --> 01:26:16,633
And whenever a train goes by a red light,
these things stop them.

1088
01:26:16,929 --> 01:26:19,681
- There's just one thing, baby!
- What's that?

1089
01:26:19,807 --> 01:26:22,262
They're all green!

1090
01:26:29,900 --> 01:26:34,692
Inspector, that short move they made
between 28th Street and 17th Street.

1091
01:26:34,822 --> 01:26:37,988
- Why'd they do that?
- I don't know.

1092
01:26:38,117 --> 01:26:40,358
Suppose they wanted to do somethin'

1093
01:26:40,494 --> 01:26:43,199
they didn't want anybody else
to know about?

1094
01:26:43,331 --> 01:26:46,830
- Like what?
- Like jumpin' off the train.

1095
01:26:46,959 --> 01:26:49,415
Turn around.
We're goin' back to 17th Street.

1096
01:26:49,545 --> 01:26:52,629
- Like hell we are!
- They are not on the train. I'm sure of it.

1097
01:26:52,756 --> 01:26:55,841
I suggested that in the first place.
You shot me down.

1098
01:26:55,968 --> 01:26:59,502
- A deadman's feature?
- They figured out how to beat that!

1099
01:26:59,638 --> 01:27:03,173
That's their plan!
That's what they started with!

1100
01:27:03,851 --> 01:27:06,472
Turn this thing around and burn rubber.

1101
01:27:11,984 --> 01:27:14,023
Guns to Mr Brown.

1102
01:27:20,409 --> 01:27:24,822
Mr Grey, would you be good enough
to give that gun to Mr Brown, please?

1103
01:27:24,955 --> 01:27:29,451
No. This ain't gonna go nowhere.
This is gonna stay with me.

1104
01:27:31,712 --> 01:27:34,285
Mr Grey, bring that gun back here, please.

1105
01:27:34,423 --> 01:27:39,548
What if they're waitin' for us up there?
I want some heavy artillery with me.

1106
01:27:39,678 --> 01:27:44,305
- Mr Grey, I won't ask you again.
- Blow it outta your ass, Mr Blue.

1107
01:27:53,108 --> 01:27:54,852
Oh, my God.

1108
01:27:57,654 --> 01:27:59,694
Let's get his money!

1109
01:28:01,617 --> 01:28:03,656
Mr Green, come on!

1110
01:28:57,589 --> 01:28:59,167
Mr Blue!

1111
01:28:59,842 --> 01:29:01,881
Did you get him?

1112
01:29:02,719 --> 01:29:07,428
You go on ahead. We'll meet
where we planned. Right?

1113
01:29:17,484 --> 01:29:22,442
- You better be right about this, Garber.
- Even if I am, it's probably too late.

1114
01:29:48,391 --> 01:29:51,391
Where are those goddamn red lights?!

1115
01:30:01,111 --> 01:30:02,605
We're not stopping!

1116
01:30:02,738 --> 01:30:05,490
There is going to be a red light!
There has to be!

1117
01:30:05,616 --> 01:30:09,234
- What if there isn't?!
- There has to be!

1118
01:30:32,768 --> 01:30:34,392
Check the emergency exits!

1119
01:30:34,520 --> 01:30:38,387
Inspector, you take 15th Street.
Officer, you take 17th Street.

1120
01:30:38,524 --> 01:30:39,935
Right, sir.

1121
01:31:06,177 --> 01:31:07,968
Are you a policeman?

1122
01:31:10,097 --> 01:31:14,177
Well done. The mayor
will go to your funeral.

1123
01:31:15,269 --> 01:31:18,638
Excuse me, fella,
would you mind droppin' that gun?

1124
01:31:19,481 --> 01:31:20,726
Drop it!

1125
01:31:35,331 --> 01:31:41,665
Officer, I suppose you couldn't use
a quarter of a million dollars, could you?

1126
01:31:41,795 --> 01:31:44,203
Quarter of a million? No, thanks.

1127
01:31:44,339 --> 01:31:49,132
My accountant says I've accepted
enough for this fiscal quarter.

1128
01:31:51,221 --> 01:31:53,629
You're the English guy on the radio.

1129
01:31:53,766 --> 01:31:55,390
Yes.

1130
01:31:56,352 --> 01:31:59,803
- Lieutenant Garber?
- Right. Do you wanna move along?

1131
01:32:00,856 --> 01:32:05,602
Excuse me... Do you people
still execute in this state?

1132
01:32:06,403 --> 01:32:09,938
What? Oh, execute.
No. Not at the moment.

1133
01:32:10,365 --> 01:32:11,990
Pity.

1134
01:32:39,395 --> 01:32:40,723
Christ!

1135
01:32:56,787 --> 01:33:01,615
We'll have an ambulance here in no time,
miss. Everything's gonna be OK.

1136
01:33:07,923 --> 01:33:10,544
Where are those goddamn red lights?!

1137
01:33:10,884 --> 01:33:12,592
Oh, God!

1138
01:33:15,097 --> 01:33:15,927
Stop!

1139
01:33:22,896 --> 01:33:24,142
There has to be.

1140
01:33:26,525 --> 01:33:30,475
It's headin' to the South Ferry loop!
It must be goin' about 70mph!

1141
01:33:36,369 --> 01:33:38,408
My God! Look!

1142
01:33:40,414 --> 01:33:42,074
We'll never make it!

1143
01:34:16,784 --> 01:34:20,651
I told you it would stop. Didn't I?

1144
01:34:23,708 --> 01:34:25,866
42nd Street already?

1145
01:34:26,794 --> 01:34:30,209
Get that list out on the wire.
Tell 'em it's top priority.

1146
01:34:30,339 --> 01:34:32,296
Whaddaya got, Rico?

1147
01:34:32,424 --> 01:34:36,552
We got positive identification
on the three dead men. Here.

1148
01:34:39,556 --> 01:34:42,344
George Steever. Professional guy, huh?

1149
01:34:42,560 --> 01:34:45,644
- St Louis.
- Yeah, I know how to read, Rico.

1150
01:34:46,522 --> 01:34:50,389
Giuseppe Benvenuto,
alias - heh-heh - Joe Welcome.

1151
01:34:50,525 --> 01:34:53,147
- Where's the guy who fried himself?
- No card on him.

1152
01:34:53,362 --> 01:34:56,149
We got a confirm on his prints
from Immigration.

1153
01:34:56,281 --> 01:35:01,786
Name's Bernard Ryder. Mercenary
soldier. Between wars, I guess.

1154
01:35:01,912 --> 01:35:06,574
None of these guys know how to drive
a train. It's the motorman who's missin'.

1155
01:35:06,708 --> 01:35:09,912
Did you get that list of motormen
who were discharged?

1156
01:35:10,045 --> 01:35:12,085
Yeah. 78 names.

1157
01:35:12,214 --> 01:35:13,376
78?

1158
01:35:13,507 --> 01:35:15,749
Yeah, but it's not that bad.

1159
01:35:15,885 --> 01:35:18,719
Eight are dead. 22 were rehired.

1160
01:35:18,846 --> 01:35:20,885
11 are in jail.

1161
01:35:22,058 --> 01:35:24,097
26 moved away.

1162
01:35:24,977 --> 01:35:28,975
One's in a mental institution. Another
is a member of the Police Department.

1163
01:35:29,106 --> 01:35:31,728
That's our man right there.

1164
01:35:31,859 --> 01:35:35,559
Sorry to disappoint you, Zachary,
but he was accounted for.

1165
01:35:35,696 --> 01:35:38,366
- So how many does that leave?
- Only nine.

1166
01:35:38,866 --> 01:35:42,116
Only nine. All right, let's get goin'.

1167
01:35:44,914 --> 01:35:47,155
What's the name of this guy?

1168
01:35:47,291 --> 01:35:49,330
Nathaniel Muscat.

1169
01:35:50,294 --> 01:35:53,295
- What'd he get busted for?
- Narcotics.

1170
01:36:00,429 --> 01:36:02,468
This way.

1171
01:36:12,274 --> 01:36:15,394
- Who's there?
- Transit Police.

1172
01:36:15,527 --> 01:36:17,567
Just a minute.

1173
01:36:20,991 --> 01:36:23,031
What do you want?

1174
01:36:26,831 --> 01:36:29,666
Uh, nothin', fella. Our mistake.

1175
01:36:31,084 --> 01:36:33,243
A spokesman for the Transit Authority

1176
01:36:33,378 --> 01:36:35,870
noted that the subway car
carrying the hostages

1177
01:36:36,006 --> 01:36:40,502
was stopped at the South Ferry loop
by the automatic safety features

1178
01:36:40,636 --> 01:36:44,336
which are activated by any car
travelling at excessive speed.

1179
01:36:44,723 --> 01:36:48,175
- Transit Authority.
- Still gotta pay.

1180
01:36:48,435 --> 01:36:50,642
- Your name is Latimer?
- What about it?

1181
01:36:50,771 --> 01:36:53,178
Just answer the question, would ya?

1182
01:36:53,315 --> 01:36:57,776
I don't work for you guys any more.
You don't get shit from me.

1183
01:36:59,238 --> 01:37:03,283
Can you account for your
whereabouts today, Mr Latimer?

1184
01:37:03,408 --> 01:37:06,943
Are you tryin' to connect me
to that hijackin'? Forget it!

1185
01:37:07,329 --> 01:37:09,867
I've been here since 2.30 this afternoon.

1186
01:37:09,999 --> 01:37:12,869
- Are you sure?
- Sure? Ask anybody!

1187
01:37:13,418 --> 01:37:16,585
- Don't worry, we will.
- Hold it!

1188
01:37:16,797 --> 01:37:19,086
It's still gonna be 50 cents.

1189
01:37:42,197 --> 01:37:44,439
- Who's that?
- Police Department.

1190
01:37:44,575 --> 01:37:48,442
- Who?
- Harold Longman, it's the Transit Police.

1191
01:37:48,746 --> 01:37:50,156
Oh, Jesus!

1192
01:37:50,831 --> 01:37:52,242
Wait a minute!

1193
01:37:57,004 --> 01:37:59,459
Just a minute!

1194
01:38:02,968 --> 01:38:07,180
- How many more we gotta see today?
- Six, seven. I don't know.

1195
01:38:11,352 --> 01:38:15,135
Come on, Mr Longman,
we ain't got all night!

1196
01:38:19,026 --> 01:38:21,185
I'll be right out!

1197
01:38:22,988 --> 01:38:26,571
I hope he washes his hands
before he opens the door.

1198
01:38:34,583 --> 01:38:36,825
- Yes, what is it?
- Harold Longman?

1199
01:38:36,960 --> 01:38:40,045
- We'd like to ask a couple of questions.
- What about?

1200
01:38:40,172 --> 01:38:44,419
- Will you let us in?
- We'll just take one minute of your time.

1201
01:38:46,971 --> 01:38:49,592
I'm Lieutenant Patrone.
This is Lieutenant Garber.

1202
01:38:49,723 --> 01:38:52,179
I'm sorry to bother you like this.

1203
01:38:53,311 --> 01:38:56,845
- Nice place you got here, Mr Longman.
- Thanks.

1204
01:38:57,564 --> 01:39:01,396
Can you give us an account of
your whereabouts this afternoon?

1205
01:39:01,527 --> 01:39:02,393
Why?

1206
01:39:02,528 --> 01:39:04,401
- Were you at work?
- No.

1207
01:39:04,947 --> 01:39:07,865
- Why not?
- I work nights.

1208
01:39:08,200 --> 01:39:10,822
- Where do you work?
- Kennedy Airport.

1209
01:39:10,953 --> 01:39:15,081
- What do you do over there?
- I'm a... fork-lift operator.

1210
01:39:15,208 --> 01:39:18,161
I got a brother-in-law does that
over in Jersey.

1211
01:39:18,293 --> 01:39:20,370
That's interestin' work.

1212
01:39:20,504 --> 01:39:23,708
Where were you this afternoon,
Mr Longman?

1213
01:39:23,966 --> 01:39:26,670
- Why?
- You tell me where, I'll tell you why.

1214
01:39:27,261 --> 01:39:29,930
I was, uh... right here.

1215
01:39:30,139 --> 01:39:33,009
Can anyone verify that fact?

1216
01:39:34,894 --> 01:39:36,933
You said you'd tell me why.

1217
01:39:37,646 --> 01:39:41,514
- You were here all afternoon?
- I sleep in the afternoon.

1218
01:39:41,650 --> 01:39:46,063
- All afternoon?
- Well... till about an hour ago.

1219
01:39:48,740 --> 01:39:51,694
- But you heard about the hijackin'?
- What hijackin'?

1220
01:39:52,369 --> 01:39:55,157
- The subway train.
- Subway...!

1221
01:39:56,332 --> 01:40:00,246
- You gotta be kiddin'!
- Do I look like I'm kiddin'?

1222
01:40:00,377 --> 01:40:04,458
I mean, would I be here
if I was kiddin', mister?

1223
01:40:04,590 --> 01:40:07,425
Subway...! Who'd wanna
do a thing like that?

1224
01:40:07,551 --> 01:40:10,338
- Hey, Z. You got a match?
- No.

1225
01:40:10,471 --> 01:40:12,546
- You got a warrant?
- No.

1226
01:40:12,681 --> 01:40:16,513
Supreme Court says you have to have
a warrant, unless I'm under arrest.

1227
01:40:16,644 --> 01:40:21,436
The way things are goin', they're gonna
be changin' that in about 10 minutes.

1228
01:40:21,565 --> 01:40:24,270
- Mr Longman, you got a match?
- No.

1229
01:40:24,401 --> 01:40:27,604
That's all right. I'll get it at the stove.

1230
01:40:27,738 --> 01:40:30,194
I'll get it.

1231
01:40:30,324 --> 01:40:32,566
It's a little tricky.

1232
01:40:34,286 --> 01:40:36,742
Has a tendency to explode.

1233
01:40:39,958 --> 01:40:41,832
Rico, let's go.

1234
01:40:41,960 --> 01:40:44,286
Thanks, Mr Longman.

1235
01:40:45,130 --> 01:40:47,123
Mr Longman, we'll be back later.

1236
01:40:47,257 --> 01:40:51,302
Yeah? Listen, I know I got a gripe
with the TA. I know I got a bum rap.

1237
01:40:51,428 --> 01:40:54,880
But I wouldn't do anythin' as stupid
as what you just told me.

1238
01:40:55,015 --> 01:40:59,309
What do think I am? A jerk? Do me a
favour, will ya? Get the hell outta here.

1239
01:40:59,437 --> 01:41:02,722
Come on, Mr Longman. We have
to follow our leads. It's our job!

1240
01:41:02,856 --> 01:41:04,398
Yeah, yeah. Big deal.

1241
01:41:04,525 --> 01:41:09,068
Look, I got my rights. This is my home.
I want a little peace!

1242
01:41:09,196 --> 01:41:11,769
Just do me a favour.
Get the hell outta here.

1243
01:41:12,115 --> 01:41:14,274
Sorry if we bothered ya, Mr Longman.

1244
01:41:14,743 --> 01:41:15,906
Come on, Rico.

1245
01:41:16,036 --> 01:41:17,863
- Atchoo!
- Gesundheit!

